events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen had 24 points and 17 rebounds, and rookie Evan Mobley added 11 points and 11 rebounds in his fourth double-double as the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Portland Trail Blazers 107-104 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen, Mobley power Cavaliers to 107-104 win over Portland

events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 25 points, hitting a career-high 7 of 10 3-pointers, and had 13 rebounds in the Indiana Pacers’ 111-98 victory over the New York Knicks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner hits 7 3s, has 25 points in Pacers' win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Al Horford wasn't calling the Boston Celtics’ team meal a “player’s only meeting,” yet he said the squad discussed in detail their expectations for Wednesday's game against the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown nets 28, Celtics use 3rd-quarter run to beat Magic

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 18 points, nine rebounds and seven assists in his return to the lineup, and Seth Curry scored 22 points and hit a crucial jumper late to lead the Philadelphia 76ers over the Chicago Bulls 103-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Curry lead short-handed 76ers past DeRozan, Bulls

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored a season-high 33 points, OG Anunoby added 21 and the Toronto Raptors beat the Washington Wizards 109-100 on Wednesday night for their fifth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet scores 33 as Raptors beat Wizards 109-100

headlines.description: — The Brooklyn Nets are starting to look like the team that was so potent a season ago.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 32, Nets hit 22 3s in 117-108 win over Hawks

headlines.description: — There are times this season where Jaren Jackson Jr. has not played up to what is expected.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. helps Grizzlies beat Nuggets -- again

headlines.description: — Paul George had 32 points and eight assists, and Reggie Jackson scored a season-high 29 points as the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 126-115 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 32, Clippers outshoot Minnesota in 126-115 win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 31 points and 10 rebounds, Luka Donic had 23 points and 12 rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks rallied past the San Antonio Spurs 109-108 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Doncic spark rally as Mavericks top Spurs, 109-108

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — When Klay Thompson tweets a shoutout, things must be going well.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole takes the pressure off Stephen Curry, scores 31

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored seven of his 20 points during a big run early in the fourth quarter and the Sacramento Kings beat the struggling New Orleans Pelicans 112-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton sparks late run as Kings top Pelicans 112-99
